B&N Bank, a Moscow-based bank with
about $3.7 billion of assets, hired Kamal Bushi as senior
 executive director  from Russian Standard, according to an e-
mailed statement from B&N.  British-born Bushi will be responsible for developing and
promoting credit cards, the statement said.  B&N Bank reported net income of 109 million rubles ($3.6
million) for the first half of this year, according to the
statement. B&N President Mikail Shishkhanov was ranked as
